The paper proposes a novel boosting approach that leverages proximal methods for optimization. This is a machine learning optimization problem, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The paper also discusses numerical experiments on simulated and real-world data, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with data analysis and prediction accuracy, which could place it in the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. Finally, the paper mentions experiments on image data, which could suggest that it belongs to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category.
